My friends and I decided to support a local business and dine in the area. We had a lovely waitress very pleasant and attentive, however as it got later in night the temperature dropped and we asked to move inside the restaurant.  Our waitress said it was impossible since all the table were accounted for and they were at "full capacity." As we continued to dine, we continuously saw various groups of ppl entering  the "full capacity" restaurant. When we asked our waitress again about moving inside she told us no again since it was full and when one of us questioned why they were still allowing others to enter when they were full she had nothing to say. You can tell she was flustered and to try to compensate, she brought us shots of house tequila when we finally asked for the check. Our waitress was very sweet but we were extremely disappointed with management for not correcting the situation or acknowledging that they were still allowing patrons into their establishment. At one point we had to send one of our meals back to be reheated due to the cold weather. Since this was such a bad experience, sadly we will not be returning.

I was totally excited to try Catrinas when I saw on their photos that they served fajitas on the traditional iron cast pan. What a disappointment? It was used more as a several plate than delivering you a steaming hot fajita platter probably because it would have been more overcooked than the food was already. Ordered the Catrina's fajita platter (steak, chicken and shrimp). The steak was overcooked - I did ask for medium cook on it - and so was the shrimp so much so that I had to spit one out. Server was nice but very slow and forgetful. Had to ask for extra napkins and water multiple times. Then they had a DJ playing latin music cool right but it was so loud that my voice was hoarse trying to have a conversation. Too loud for the size of the restaurant. I asked if they could lower it a bit and was totally ignored. Will never go there again.
